+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **Juice Shop practicals mapped to session lifecycle stages:**         |
|                                                                       |
| -   **Stage ②:** Login with admin@juice-sh.op --- observe the JWT     |
|     token in ZAP\'s response. Decode it at jwt.io. What claims does   |
|     it contain?                                                       |
|                                                                       |
| -   **Stage ③:** Juice Shop issues a JWT signed with a weak secret    |
|     (\"secret\" or a common word). Use flask-unsign or jwt-cracker to |
|     recover it. Forge an admin token.                                 |
|                                                                       |
| -   **Stage ④:** Cookie stealing practical: BeEF\'s \"Get Cookie\"    |
|     command demonstrates what XSS yields from a session without the   |
|     HttpOnly flag.                                                    |
|                                                                       |
| -   **Stage ⑤:** View Basket challenge: change the basket ID in the   |
|     /rest/basket/:id request to another user\'s ID in ZAP. Observe    |
|     that Juice Shop returns it --- a live IDOR.                       |
|                                                                       |
| -   **Stage ⑥:** After logging out of Juice Shop, replay the old JWT  |
|     in ZAP\'s Repeater. Does it still work? What does this tell you   |
|     about Juice Shop\'s session invalidation?                         |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **The session security principle:** a session token is a temporary,
  delegated credential --- it carries the same privileges as the user\'s
  password for its entire lifetime. Every control that protects the
  password (not transmitted in clear, not stored in readable form,
  invalidated after use) should also apply to the session token.

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
